        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "Hermansky-Pudlak syndrome with pulmonary fibrosis as a complication includes two types (HPS-1 and HPS-4) of Hermansky-Pudlak syndrome (HPS; see this term) a multi-system disorder characterized by oculocutaneous albinism bleeding diathesis and in some cases pulmonary fibrosis or granulomatous colitis."
